{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread\/setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"enabled"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default, for every thread, is that they are enabled (as if called with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enabled"},{"type":"text","text":" being "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Those checks are conservative. That means that they will only succeed in considering a call thread-safe (and therefore allow it to happen) if the engine can guarantee such safety."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because of that, there may be cases where the user may want to disable them ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enabled"},{"type":"text","text":" being "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") to make certain operations allowed again. By doing so, it becomes the user’s responsibility to ensure thread safety (e.g., by using ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") for those objects that are otherwise protected by the engine."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is an advanced usage of the engine. You are advised to use it only if you know what you are doing and there is no safer way.","type":"text"}]}]},{"name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is useful for scripts running on either arbitrary "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" objects or tasks submitted to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". It doesn’t apply to code running during "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node"},{"type":"text","text":" group processing, where the checks will be always performed."}]}],"type":"aside"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even in the case of having disabled the checks in a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool"},{"text":" task, there’s no need to re-enable them at the end. The engine will do so.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Sets whether the thread safety checks the engine normally performs in methods of certain classes (e.g., ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node"},{"type":"text","text":") should happen "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"on the current thread","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/thread\/setthreadsafetychecksenabled(_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLan